to research. Research Use may be performed by an individual or organization,
including a for-profit organization, only when the Software and its outputs are
not used for Commercial Use or Production Use.

"Commercial Use" means using the Software or its outputs to sell, license,
rent, monetize, provide, develop, improve, or validate a product or service; to
perform a fee-based service for a third party; or otherwise to obtain a direct
commercial benefit. Internal evaluation by a for-profit organization is not
Commercial Use when it is limited to deciding whether to seek a separate
commercial license.

"Production Use" means using the Software or its outputs in a live,
customer-facing, revenue-generating, or operational system or business process,
including automated or assisted decisions that affect a person, property,
rights, access, eligibility, employment, credit, insurance, healthcare, safety,
or money.

